reviewText: I was very excited to get this, but I am disappointed with it.  It's really short and just not done very well.
A little slow but worth watching. Highlights the importance of breastmilk but focuses too much on preemies. Still, a good movie.

This is a compelling film about the need of mother's milk for fragile babies. It's so endearing; it draws you into loss and success as experienced by a few families. The film really depicts the need for milk-banking in the U.S. Something that has a stronger presence in many other countries.
